com.avaya.csta.binding

Class OriginalCallInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.OriginalCallInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class OriginalCallInfo
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Avaya Original Call Information Private Data.
    OriginalCallInfo Parameters
    reason reason Specifies the reason for the Original Call Information. The following reasons are supported:
    • none
    • conferenced
    • consultation
    • transferred
    • newCall
    networkCallingDevice CallingDeviceID Specifies the Original calling device.
    networkCalledDevice CalledDeviceID Specifies the Original called device.
    acdGroup DeviceID Specifies the ACD split extension to which the call is delivered. This parameter applies when callCharacteristics is ACD call.
    trunkGroup String Specifies the original Trunk Group received by the active call.
    trunkMember String Specifies the original Trunk Member received by the active call.
    lookAheadInfo LookAheadInfo Specifies the original lookAheadInfo received by the active call.
    userEnteredCode UserEnteredCode Specifies the original userEnteredCode received by the active call.
    userData UserData Specifies the original userData received by the active call.
    callLinkageData CallLinkageData Specifies the original callLinkageData received by the active call.
    deviceHistory DeviceHistory Specifies a list of deviceIDs that were previously associated with the call.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
